entry.sense:
qaAbalahu binafosihi [He opposed himself to him]. (TA, art. ErD.) 
See EaraDa lahu; 
and see 4.

Astqblhu bimaA yakorahu 
(A, Ḳ, in art. bkt, &c.) 
He encountered him with, or, as it often means, he accused him, to his face, of a thing that he disliked, or hated: 
see bak-atahu; 
and the phrases Aalbohtu QsotiqobaAluka OaxaAka bimaA layosa fiyhi 
and qaAbalahu↓ biAlkacbi, voce bahatahu; 
and Astqblhu biAlHaq-i, voce qaraHahu; 
in both senses like laqiyahu bimakoruwhK.

mino ciI qabalK: 
see mino ciI EawoDK; 
and see qibalN; and OunufN.

UiqobaAlapN and its syn. UiqobaAlN: 
see 4; 
and see UidobaArapN.

huwa AlfaHolu laA yuqodaEu Oanofuhu: 
see OanofN; 
and see qrE.

qaduwmN 
An adz; 
[so in the present day, but pronounced qad-uwm;] a certain implement of the carpenter; (Ṣ, Mgh, Mṣb;) a faOos with which one hews, or forms or fashions by cutting. (Ṣ.)

3. qaATaEahu 
He separated himself from him, with the latter's concurrence; 
see faArazahu; 
and see AinoqaTaEa Eanohu.

4. Oaqolaqahu 
He, or it, disquieted him; disturbed him; agitated him; flurried him. (Ṣ, Mṣb.) He moved it, a thing, from its place; 
as also qal-aqahu↓. (M.)

1. qam-ahu: 
see 4; 
and vam-ahu, in two places.

qanaA, aor. yaqonuw, 
inf. n. qunuw-N; 
a dial. var. of qanaOa, q. v. (TA.)

2. qaw-amahu 
He made it straight, or even; namely, a crooked thing; 
as also OaqaAmahu↓: (TḲ:) and made it right, or in a right condition; direct, or rightly directed.

qaAYimN 
Appearing; conspicuous; 
[as though standing before one]: said of a thing whether standing or thrown down. (TA, in explanation of the phrase hecaA nuSobu EayoniI, art. nSb.)

qaAYimapN A leg of a table, and of a throne, or moveable seat, &c. (JK.) 
See also qaAmapN; 
and see UisonaAdN.
